# Question-Answer Best Practices

## Communication Style
- Provide clear and concise answers
- Prefer brevity unless the user explicitly asks for more detail
- Focus on directly answering the question asked
- Avoid unnecessary explanations or tangents

## Content Quality
- Ensure answers are accurate and well-researched
- Provide sources or references when appropriate
- Use simple, straightforward language
- Structure complex answers with clear formatting

## User Interaction
- Adapt response length to the user's needs
- Offer additional details only when requested
- Clarify ambiguous questions before answering
- Provide examples when they enhance understanding

## Efficiency
- Answer promptly and directly
- Avoid redundant information
- Use bullet points or numbered lists for clarity
- Summarize key points when appropriate